cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper proposes a novel method for dynamic texture synthesis using kernel learning and extreme learning machine. The paper focuses on computer vision and machine learning techniques, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The use of kernel learning and ELM also suggests that it could belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The paper also mentions experiments on benchmark datasets, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category. The use of similarity correlation and modeling of frame-to-frame transitions suggests that it could belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Finally, the use of texture synthesis suggests that it could belong to the cs.GR (Graphics) sub-category.
